  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I get call history for my Airtel prepaid number?",
  "response": "To obtain the call history for your Airtel prepaid number, you have several options. However, it's important to note that Airtel may provide limited call history details for prepaid users compared to postpaid accounts. Here's how you can access your call history:\n\n### 1. **My Airtel App**\n\nAirtel's official mobile application, **My Airtel**, allows you to manage your account, view usage, and access some call details.\n\n**Steps:**\n1. **Download and Install**: If you haven't already, download the My Airtel app from the [Google Play Store](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=in.Airtel.app&hl=en&gl=US) or the [Apple App Store](https://apps.apple.com/in/app/my-airtel/id432562274).\n2. **Login/Register**: Open the app and log in using your Airtel mobile number. If you're a new user, follow the on-screen instructions to register.\n3. **Navigate to Usage or Call History**: Once logged in, navigate to the **\"Usage\"** or **\"My Account\"** section. Here, you may find details about your call history, including incoming and outgoing calls along with their durations and timestamps.\n\n### 2. **Airtel Online Account**\n\nAccessing your Airtel account through the official website can also provide call details.\n\n**Steps:**\n1. **Visit the Airtel Website**: Go to the [Airtel Official Website](https://www.airtel.in/).\n2. **Login to My Account**: Click on the **\"My Account\"** option and log in using your Airtel number and password. If you haven't set up an online account yet, you'll need to register.\n3. **Check Call History**: Once logged in, navigate to the **\"Usage Details\"** or **\"Call History\"** section to view your call records.\n\n### 3. **SMS Services**\n\nAirtel provides certain SMS codes that can be used to retrieve account information, including some call details.\n\n**Example:**\n- **Check Balance and Usage**: Dial `*123#` and follow the prompts to view your balance and some usage details. While this might not provide a detailed call history, it can give you an overview of your recent activity.\n\n**Note**: SMS-based call history retrieval may offer limited information. For more comprehensive details, the My Airtel app or online account is recommended.\n\n### 4. **Customer Care**\n\nIf you're unable to access your call history through the app or website, contacting Airtel's customer support is a reliable option.\n\n**Steps:**\n1. **Call Airtel Customer Care**: Dial `121` from your Airtel prepaid number. This is Airtel's toll-free customer care number in India.\n2. **Navigate the IVR**: Follow the interactive voice response (IVR) prompts to reach the customer service representative.\n3. **Request Call History**: Inform the representative that you'd like to obtain your call history. They may provide the required details or guide you on how to access them.\n\n**Alternative Contact Methods:**\n- **Email Support**: You can also reach out to Airtel support via email through the [Airtel Contact Page](https://www.airtel.in/support/).\n- **Visit an Airtel Store**: For in-person assistance, visit your nearest Airtel store where a representative can help you access your call history.\n\n### 5. **Airtel Store or Retailer**\n\nVisiting an Airtel store or authorized retailer can provide personalized assistance.\n\n**Steps:**\n1. **Find a Store**: Locate your nearest Airtel store using the [Airtel Store Locator](https://locator.airtel.in/).\n2. **Bring Identification**: Take a valid ID and your Airtel prepaid number details for verification.\n3. **Request Call History**: Speak with the store representative to request access to your call history.\n\n### **Important Considerations**\n\n- **Data Availability**: Airtel may store call history data for a limited period (e.g., last few months). If you need older records, they might not be available through standard channels.\n- **Privacy and Security**: Ensure that you protect your account information and only share necessary details with authorized Airtel representatives.\n- **Service Limitations**: Prepaid accounts might have restrictions on the depth of call history accessible compared to postpaid accounts.\n\nIf you encounter any issues or require detailed call records beyond the available options, contacting Airtel's customer support is the best course of action.",
